TObjectPtr<ULFPGameInstance> CachedGameInstance;

// In Setup
CachedGameInstance = GI;

// Usage
if (CachedGameInstance)
{
    Text_Gold->SetText(FText::FromString(
        FString::Printf(TEXT("金币: %d"), CachedGameInstance->GetGold())));
}
```

---

## 12. State Management Pattern

Widgets track UI state separately:

```cpp
// Selection state
int32 SelectedRelicIndex = INDEX_NONE;

// Placement tracking
TArray<bool> PlacedStates;

// Update state and UI accordingly
void MarkUnitPlaced(int32 PartyIndex, bool bPlaced)
{
    if (!PlacedStates.IsValidIndex(PartyIndex)) return;

    PlacedStates[PartyIndex] = bPlaced;
    UpdateSlotVisual(PartyIndex);  // Update UI based on state
}
```

---

## 13. Visibility Control Pattern

Standard approach for showing/hiding widgets:

```cpp
void OnCloseClicked()
{
    SetVisibility(ESlateVisibility::Collapsed);  // Hide widget
    RemoveFromParent();  // Remove from parent
    OnClosed.Broadcast();  // Notify listeners
}
```

**Common visibility states**:
- `ESlateVisibility::Visible` - Fully visible, takes space
- `ESlateVisibility::Collapsed` - Hidden, doesn't take space
- `ESlateVisibility::Hidden` - Hidden, but takes space

---

## 14. Optional Binding Pattern

Handle missing widgets gracefully:

```cpp
void RefreshDetailPanel()
{
    if (Text_SelectedName) Text_SelectedName->SetText(Definition.DisplayName);
    if (Text_SelectedDescription) Text_SelectedDescription->SetText(...);
    if (Text_SelectedPrice) Text_SelectedPrice->SetText(...);
    if (Button_Purchase) Button_Purchase->SetIsEnabled(!bOwned && bCanAfford);
}
```

This allows widgets to work even if some optional elements are missing from the UMG designer.

