## 16. Widget Input Handling (Special Cases)

For widgets that need to detect which button was clicked:

```cpp
void OnRelicButtonClicked()
{
    for (const auto& Pair : ButtonToRelicIndexMap)
    {
        if (Pair.Key && Pair.Key->IsHovered())  // Check which button is hovered
        {
            SelectedRelicIndex = Pair.Value;
            RefreshDetailPanel();
            return;
        }
    }
}
```

For pressed state checking:
```cpp
void OnDestinationClicked()
{
    for (const auto& Pair : ButtonToNodeIDMap)
    {
        if (Pair.Key && Pair.Key->IsPressed())  // Check pressed state
        {
            OnTeleportTargetSelected.Broadcast(Pair.Value);
            return;
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 17. Event Binding to Game World Objects

For widgets that need to respond to game events:

```cpp
// In HealthBarWidget
void BindToUnit(ALFPTacticsUnit* Unit)
{
    if (!Unit || BoundUnit == Unit) return;

    UnbindFromUnit();  // Clean up old bindings

    BoundUnit = Unit;

    // Subscribe to unit events
    BoundUnit->OnHealthChangedDelegate.AddDynamic(this, &ULFPHealthBarWidget::OnHealthChanged);
    BoundUnit->OnDeathDelegate.AddDynamic(this, &ULFPHealthBarWidget::OnUnitDeath);

    UpdateHealthBar(BoundUnit->GetCurrentHealth(), BoundUnit->GetMaxHealth());
    SetVisibility(ESlateVisibility::Visible);
}
```

**Proper cleanup**:
```cpp
void UnbindFromUnit()
{
    if (BoundUnit)
    {
        BoundUnit->OnHealthChangedDelegate.RemoveDynamic(this, &ULFPHealthBarWidget::OnHealthChanged);
        BoundUnit->OnDeathDelegate.RemoveDynamic(this, &ULFPHealthBarWidget::OnUnitDeath);
        BoundUnit = nullptr;
    }
    SetVisibility(ESlateVisibility::Hidden);
}
```

---

## 18. Turn Manager Event Binding Pattern

Widgets can subscribe to global game events:

```cpp
void ULFPTurnSpeedListWidget::InitializeTurnOrder()
{
    if (!TurnManagerRef)
    {
        TArray<AActor*> FoundManagers;
        UGameplayStatics::GetAllActorsOfClass(GetWorld(), ALFPTurnManager::StaticClass(), FoundManagers);
        if (FoundManagers.Num() > 0)
        {
            TurnManagerRef = Cast<ALFPTurnManager>(FoundManagers[0]);
        }
    }

    if (TurnManagerRef)
    {
        // Bind to turn manager events
        TurnManagerRef->OnTurnChanged.AddDynamic(this, &ULFPTurnSpeedListWidget::OnTurnChanged);
        TurnManagerRef->OnPhaseChanged.AddDynamic(this, &ULFPTurnSpeedListWidget::OnPhaseChanged);

        UpdateTurnOrder();
    }
}
```

---

## 19. Complete Widget Structure Template

Here's a minimal template showing all the standard patterns:

```cpp
// .h file
UCLASS()
class LFP2D_API ULFPMyWidget : public UUserWidget
{
    GENERATED_BODY()

public:
    UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category = "MyWidget")
    void Setup(const FMyDataDefinition& InData);

    UPROPERTY(BlueprintAssignable)
    FOnMyWidgetClosed OnClosed;

protected:
    virtual void NativeOnInitialized() override;

private:
    void RefreshUI();

    UFUNCTION() void OnButtonClicked();
    UFUNCTION() void OnCloseClicked();

    // BindWidget elements
    UPROPERTY(BlueprintReadOnly, meta = (BindWidgetOptional))
    TObjectPtr<UTextBlock> Text_Title;

    UPROPERTY(BlueprintReadOnly, meta = (BindWidgetOptional))
    TObjectPtr<UButton> Button_Close;

    // Cached data
    FMyDataDefinition CachedData;
};

// .cpp file
void ULFPMyWidget::NativeOnInitialized()
{
    Super::NativeOnInitialized();

    if (Button_Close) Button_Close->OnClicked.AddDynamic(this, &ULFPMyWidget::OnCloseClicked);
}

void ULFPMyWidget::Setup(const FMyDataDefinition& InData)
{
    CachedData = InData;
    RefreshUI();
}

void ULFPMyWidget::RefreshUI()
{
    if (Text_Title) Text_Title->SetText(CachedData.DisplayName);
}

void ULFPMyWidget::OnCloseClicked()
{
    SetVisibility(ESlateVisibility::Collapsed);
    RemoveFromParent();
    OnClosed.Broadcast();
}
```

---

## Summary of Key Patterns

1. **Always use BindWidget/BindWidgetOptional** for UMG Designer integration
2. **Implement NativeOnInitialized() or NativeConstruct()** to bind delegates
3. **Use Setup() function** for data initialization
4. **Cache references** to GameInstance and data structures
5. **Use separate Refresh() functions** for different UI sections
6. **Store button→data mappings** for dynamically created elements
7. **Declare BlueprintAssignable delegates** for parent communication
8. **Always null-check widgets** before using them
9. **Use UFUNCTION() macro** on all callback methods
10. **Bind/unbind properly** to avoid memory leaks when binding to game objects
11. **Use TObjectPtr<>** for object references in UObject-derived classes
12. **Handle optional widgets gracefully** with BindWidgetOptional

